description: Latin annumeratus, past participle of annumerare.

verbs.description: annumerate (third-person singular simple present annumerates, present participle annumerating, simple past and past participle annumerated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To add on; to count in.
examples: There are omissions of other kinds, which will deserve to be annumerated to these by being either total, or notorious, or upon the score of some other circumstance
